explanation: This solution iterates over the string with a sliding window of size from minSize to maxSize. For each window, it counts the occurrences of substrings with unique characters less than or equal to maxLetters. It keeps track of the maximum count and returns it. The time complexity is O(n*m) where n is the length of the string and m is the maximum window size. The space complexity is O(n) for storing the count of substrings.

